@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
    ViewBag.Title = "DripSphere OS™ – Smart Irrigation Platform – Drip Smart USA";
    ViewBag.MetaDescription = "DripSphere OS™ is DripSmart's smart irrigation and fertigation control platform. Monitor, schedule, and automate your entire irrigation system from your phone.";
}

<section class="page-hero" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a1535 0%, #181F4E 60%, #1a3a7a 100%);">
    <div class="container page-hero-inner">
        <div class="page-hero-text">
            <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/digital-farming">Digital Farming</a> / <span>DripSphere OS™</span></nav>
            <div style="display:inline-block; background:var(--blue); color:white; font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:20px; margin-bottom:16px;">Platform</div>
            <h1 style="color:white;">DripSphere OS™</h1>
            <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85); font-size:1.2rem;">Smart irrigation and fertigation control — right from your phone. Schedule zones, monitor soil moisture, track water use, and automate fertigation across your entire operation.</p>
            <div style="display:flex; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:28px;">
                <a href="/find-a-dealer" class="btn-primary">Get It Through a Dealer</a>
                <a href="/digital-farming" class="btn-outline-white">Back to Digital Farming</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Core Features -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Platform Features</span>
            <h2>Everything Your Irrigation System Needs. In One App.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="two-col-layout" style="margin-top:48px; gap:24px;">
            <div class="info-card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="smartphone"></i></div>
                <h3>Mobile Control</h3>
                <p>Run, pause, or adjust any irrigation zone from anywhere with a cell signal. No need to be in the field to manage your system — schedule a zone while you're at the shop or at home.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="thermometer"></i></div>
                <h3>Soil Moisture Monitoring</h3>
                <p>Wireless soil moisture and temperature sensors feed real-time data into DripSphere OS™. Set threshold-based irrigation triggers so water runs when the soil actually needs it — not on a fixed clock.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="flask-conical"></i></div>
                <h3>Precision Fertigation Control</h3>
                <p>Program fertilizer injection schedules by zone, crop stage, and product. DripSphere OS™ controls injection pumps and EC/pH monitoring inline — delivering exactly what your crop needs, when it needs it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="bar-chart-2"></i></div>
                <h3>Water Use Reporting</h3>
                <p>Every irrigation event is logged automatically — volume, duration, zone, and date. Generate reports for lender compliance, water district filings, or your own agronomic records.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="cloud"></i></div>
                <h3>Weather Integration</h3>
                <p>DripSphere OS™ connects to local weather station data and ET (evapotranspiration) models — automatically adjusting irrigation schedules based on actual crop water demand, not guesswork.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="alert-circle"></i></div>
                <h3>Alerts & Diagnostics</h3>
                <p>Receive instant push notifications for pressure anomalies, flow deviations, or sensor disconnects — catching system problems before they cost you a crop.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Hardware -->
<section class="section" style="background:var(--blue-pale);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout" style="align-items:center;">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">The Hardware</span>
                <h2>Controllers & Sensors Built for the Field</h2>
                <p>DripSphere OS™ runs on a family of field-hardened controllers and wireless sensors — designed to work in the harshest agricultural environments without babysitting.</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:24px;">
                    <li><strong>DS-Controller Pro:</strong> 8- and 16-zone controllers with cellular connectivity and battery backup</li>
                    <li><strong>DS-Soil Sensor:</strong> Wireless capacitive soil moisture and temperature sensors, 5-year battery life</li>
                    <li><strong>DS-FlowMeter:</strong> Inline pulse flow meters for real-time water use tracking per zone</li>
                    <li><strong>DS-Injector:</strong> Proportional injection pump controllers for single and multi-channel fertigation</li>
                    <li><strong>DS-Gateway:</strong> Cellular-to-field bridge for farms without reliable WiFi coverage</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="benefit-stat-card" style="align-self:start;">
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">16</span><span class="big-label">Zones per controller</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">5yr</span><span class="big-label">Wireless sensor battery life</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">4G LTE</span><span class="big-label">Cellular connectivity standard</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">IP67</span><span class="big-label">Controller weatherproof rating</span></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Compatibility -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Works With What You Have</span>
            <h2>Compatible With Existing Irrigation Infrastructure</h2>
            <p style="max-width:620px; margin:16px auto 0;">DripSphere OS™ controllers work with standard 24VAC solenoid valves — meaning it can be added to most existing drip systems, not just new DripSmart installations. Your dealer can assess compatibility during a site visit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid" style="margin-top:40px;">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="check-circle"></i></div>
                <h3>New DripSmart Systems</h3>
                <p>DripSphere OS™ is natively compatible with all new DripSmart system installations — controllers, sensors, and emitters are pre-configured as a matched system.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="refresh-cw"></i></div>
                <h3>Existing Drip Systems</h3>
                <p>If your current system uses standard 24VAC solenoid valves, DripSphere OS™ controllers can typically be added without replacing your laterals or emitters.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="handshake"></i></div>
                <h3>Third-Party Sensors</h3>
                <p>DripSphere OS™ supports Modbus and standard 0–10V sensor inputs — allowing integration with third-party soil sensors and weather stations you may already have.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="section" style="background:var(--midnight); color:white;">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <h2 style="color:white;">DripSphere OS™ Is Configured and Installed by Certified Dealers</h2>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75); max-width:580px; margin:16px auto 0;">Proper setup — sensor placement, zone mapping, fertigation programming — is what separates a smart system that performs from one that sits unused. Your local dealer handles it all.</p>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:16px; justify-content:center; margin-top:32px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <a href="/find-a-dealer" class="btn-primary">Find a Certified Dealer</a>
            <a href="/digital-farming/fertigation" class="btn-outline-white">Learn About Precision Fertigation</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
